Question_1.Context: The study evaluated the inhibition potential of anti-inflammatory compounds isolated from Pterocarpus erinaceus and Discoglypremna caloneura on Mpro. The compounds were tested for their inhibitory effect against SARS-CoV-2 Mpro.
Question_1.Question: What was the IC50 value of the acetoxy product (compound 3) in the inhibition assay against SARS-CoV-2 Mpro?
Question_1.Source: Among the effectively tested samples, two derivatized compounds displayed significant improvement on the activity from the starting material, friedelin (1) through the acetoreduced (2) to the acetoxy product (3) with respective IC50 values of 42.89, 29.69 and 19.39 µg/mL.

Question_2.Context: The study focused on the inhibitory effect of compounds isolated from Pterocarpus erinaceus and Discoglypremna caloneura on SARS-CoV-2 Mpro.
Question_2.Question: Which compound showed the highest activity among the tested samples, although lower compared to baicalein?
Question_2.Source: The latter displayed the highest activity although lower as compared to that of baicalein, the positive control with IC50 0.41 µg/mL.
